RPC-mode.md — Protocol-level state machine analysis of the RPC mode from the client's perspective, covering: message format (responses and events), client-side states (IDLE, PROMPT_PENDING, CANCELING, COMPACT_PENDING) with sub-states for pending permission/question replies, state transitions driven by sent commands and received responses, full command reference with parameters and expected responses, event reference, correlation ID semantics, lifecycles for steering/follow-up/permission/question/cancellation, protocol-level ambiguities, and eight required invariants.
